name: FA Cup
summary: The FA Cup, England's oldest cup competition, has made significant changes to its format, eliminating replays and moving the final to the penultimate weekend of the season. This decision has sparked mixed reactions, with some praising its streamlining effect and others criticizing its potential impact on lower division clubs. This weekend's semifinals feature tantalizing matchups between Manchester City and Chelsea, as well as Liverpool and Manchester United, raising questions about the potential for upsets and the overall excitement surrounding the tournament. Despite the changes, the FA Cup remains a prestigious competition, with ESPN platforms set to broadcast the semifinals and the final, while other outlets delve into the implications of the format overhaul.
